macro.title: Total pending home sales reach multiyear high with mortgage rates near 6%
macro.what: This year we have benefited from mortgage rates remaining below 6.64% for the last 16 weeks, spurring total pending home sales.
macro.why: Rates & inflation shape discount rates and housing affordability.
macro.market: Lower rates support demand/valuations; higher rates pressure builders/REITs and slow transactions.

macro.title: With Powell set to move on, who are the candidates for the next Fed chair?
macro.what: With Jerome Powell's term ending in May, several candidates are in the running to become the next Federal Reserve chair.
macro.why: Rates & inflation shape discount rates and housing affordability.
macro.market: Lower rates support demand/valuations; higher rates pressure builders/REITs and slow transactions.

macro.title: Mortgage Rates to Hold Firm as Delayed Jobs Report Shows Unemployment at 4-Year High
macro.what: Rates will stay mostly steady today after the delayed September jobs report showed both a rising unemployment rate, and strong but concentrated jobs growth in the private sector
macro.why: Rates & inflation shape discount rates and housing affordability.
macro.market: Lower rates support demand/valuations; higher rates pressure builders/REITs and slow transactions.

macro.title: Home Prices Post Biggest Gain in 7 Months Despite Slow Demand
macro.what: Would-be homebuyers are sitting on the sidelines, wary of economic uncertainty and still-high housing costs
macro.why: Price trend signals wealth effects and buyer/seller power.
macro.market: Firm prices help builder margins; softness hits comps and sentiment.

macro.title: It’s the Strongest Buyer’s Market in Records Dating Back Over a Decade
macro.what: Home sellers outnumbered buyers by a record 36.8% in October, giving buyers who were in the market room to negotiate
macro.why: Relevant development for housing and markets.
macro.market: Watch second-order effects across builders, lenders, and REITs.
